<p>Example #0: Simple PHP Output with Hyperlink</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">
&lt;?php
echo "<p>Welcome</p>";
echo "<p>This is an example</p>";
echo "<p><a href=\"http://www.hfcc.edu/\">Henry Ford College</a></p>";
echo '<p><a href="http://www.hfcc.edu/">Henry Ford College</a></p>';
?>
</code></pre>
<p><a href="ex0.php">Run it now</a></p>

<p>Example #1: Simple PHP Echo/Date Function</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">
&lt;?php
echo "<p>'Hello John'</p>";
echo "<p>Hello \'John\'</p>";
echo "<p>Hello 'John'</p>";
echo "Today is " . date("Y-m-d") . "<br>";
?>
</code></pre>
<p><a href="ex0.php">Run it now</a></p>

<p>Example #2: Simple PHP Echo/Random/Round Fuction</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">
&lt;?php
$text = " This program randomly generates a number between -10 through 120, after the number is generated, its converts the number from Fahrenheit into Celsius. The number is: ";
$random = rand(-10,120);
$cel = ($random - 32) * (5/9);
echo $text;
echo(round($cel));
?>
</code></pre>
<p><a href="ex0.php">Run it now</a></p>

<p>Example #3: Simple PHP Echo/If/Variable Statement</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">
&lt;?php

$money = "$";
$text = "Your grosspay is: ";
$gross = 5000;
if ($gross >= 20000)
{
	echo "<p>You are making over $20,000 per year</p>";
	echo $text;
	echo $money;
	echo $gross;
}
	
if ($gross <= 20000)
{
	echo "<p>You are making less than $20,000 per year</p>";
	echo $text;
	echo $money;
	echo $gross;
}
?>
</code></pre>
<p><a href="ex0.php">Run it now</a></p>

<p>Example #4: Simple PHP Echo/If/Elseif Statement</p>
<pre><code class="language-php">
&lt;?php
$text = "Your age is";
$age = 22; 
if ($age >= 21)
{
	echo "<p>You are over or of the age of 21</p>";
	echo $text;
	echo $age;
}
elseif ($age >= 18) 
{
	echo "<p>You are not over the age of 21</p>";
	echo "<p>You are over or of the age of 18</p>";
}
elseif ($age < 18) 
	echo "<p>You are a minor who is under the age of 18</p>"
?>
</code></pre>
<p><a href="ex0.php">Run it now</a></p>
